        <txttip left="738" top="91" right="881" bottom="115" content="192.68.0.2/24" fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="140" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-1" charset="1" />
        <txttip left="184" top="233" right="1437" bottom="432" content="1. Start up the devices&#x0D;&#x0A;2. Set the Name, IP address and subnet mask for PC1 and PC2(Subnet Mask is 255.255.255.0)&#x0D;&#x0A;3. Test connectivity between PC1 and PC2&#x0D;&#x0A;   a) Use PC1 to ping PC2&#x0D;&#x0A;   b) use PC2 to ping PC1&#x0D;&#x0A;NOTE: Both pings should be successful. If not, check your IP addresses&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;4. Capture ping data/packets(using Wireshark) at Eth0/0/1 of PC1 and examine the different parts of the captured info.&#x0D;&#x0A;5. Save the completed work as &apos;Firstname-userID-Lab1&apos;, zip the resulting folder and upload the zip file to the lms." fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="140" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-2044184" charset="1" />
    </txttips>
